@startuml uml_class_gateway
title LLD — api-gateway (HTTP façade + downstream clients)
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica

package "Presentation (Express)" {
  class "Express application\n(server.ts)" as App <<Node>> {
    listen()
  }
  class "Route table\n(/api/* → service HTTP)" as Routes {
    forward()
  }
  class "Auth middleware" as AuthMw {
    validate JWT
    set x-user-id
  }
}

package "Integration — typed clients" {
  class "HTTP proxy / fetch\n(per service URL)" as HttpC
  class "gRPC client stubs\n(proto/*.proto)" as GrpcC {
    AuthService
    BookingService
    ListingsService
    MessagingService
    TrustService
    AnalyticsService
    MediaService
    NotificationService
  }
}

App --> Routes
Routes --> AuthMw
AuthMw --> HttpC : REST to services
AuthMw --> GrpcC : same contracts as\nservice **grpc-server.ts**

note bottom of GrpcC
  Each microservice **implements** the
  RPCs in its **grpc-server.ts**; protos
  are the cross-process **interface**.
  Gateway may call gRPC where wired, and
  HTTP elsewhere — both map to the same
  domain operations.
end note

@enduml
